Insider Activity


Individual




John J. Greisch



Mr. John J. Greisch is Independent Non-Executive Director at Actelion Ltd., President & Chief Executive Officer at Hill-Rom, Inc., and President, CEO & Executive Director at Hill-Rom Holdings, Inc. He is on the Board of Directors at Actelion Ltd., Hill-Rom Holdings, Inc., Children's Memorial Foundation, Shedd Aquarium Society, Ann & Robert H. Lurie Children's Hospital of Chicago, and Advanced Medical Technology Association.
Mr. Greisch was previously employed as President-International & Vice President by Baxter International, Inc., President-International Operations by Baxter BioScience Corp., President & Chief Executive Officer by FleetPride, Inc., and President, Chief Financial Officer & Treasurer by Interlake Corp. He also served on the board at TomoTherapy, Inc.
He received his undergraduate degree from Miami University (Ohio) and a graduate degree from Northwestern University.



